               <p>NATHANIEL MASON. I live in <placeName id="t18250407-185-crimeloc1012">Burton-crescent</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18250407-185-crimeloc1012" type="placeName" value="Burton-crescent"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18250407-185-crimeloc1012" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250407-185-off1010 t18250407-185-crimeloc1012"></join>; the prisoner was employed as a <rs id="t18250407-185-deflabel1013" type="occupation">needle-woman</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250407-185-defend975 t18250407-185-deflabel1013"></join> in my family; these shirts are my property, and have my mark on them. I had not missed them till I received information of their being lost.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250407-185-person978">
                  HARRIET 
                  WILLIAMS
               <interp inst="t18250407-185-person978" type="surname" value="WILLIAMS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250407-185-person978" type="given" value="HARRIET"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250407-185-person978" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am servant to Mr. Mason. I missed a spoon from a basket on the table, in the kitchen, between twelve and one o'clock on the 29th of March; the prisoner had not then left the house. Miss Mason asked her, in my presence, if she had got it; she denied it at first - but afterwards produced it from her pocket, when Miss Mason said she would search her.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250407-185-person979">
                  HENRY 
                  WILLIAM RUSSELL
               <interp inst="t18250407-185-person979" type="surname" value="WILLIAM RUSSELL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250407-185-person979" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250407-185-person979" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a pawnbroker. The two shirts were pawned at our shop, one on the 11th of February, the other on the 25th, and the shifts, on the 21st of December, by the prisoner.</p>
               <p>FRANCES MASON. I am sister of the prosecutor; these articles are ours - they were kept in a drawer in the bedroom; the prisoner had access to them.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250407-185-person980">
                  JOHN 
                  LIMBRICK
               <interp inst="t18250407-185-person980" type="surname" value="LIMBRICK"></interp>
